description._content: Description: Landing of His Excellency Sir Charles Bruce, G.C.M.G., on 8th November, 1903. Sir C. Bruce is dressed in black and is wearing a white helmet. Location: Seychelles Date: 08 November 1903 Description: Police Guard of Honour waiting for His Excellency Sir C. Bruce, G.C.M.G., on his landing on 8th November, 1903. Location: Seychelles Date: 08 November 1903 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/771 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
